00:25:29,724 --> 00:25:33,956
Now I've never been to Newfoundland before,
but I've met many Newfies in my travels

409
00:25:34,044 --> 00:25:36,512
and I can't wait to meet some more.

410
00:25:41,404 --> 00:25:43,554
I'm on a journey to the edge of the world.

411
00:25:43,644 --> 00:25:45,874
I'm leaving Nova Scotia and I'm flying north

412
00:25:45,964 --> 00:25:48,922
to the island of Newfoundland
and St John's.

413
00:25:49,044 --> 00:25:52,957
It was here on this rocky shoreline that
some of the earliest European explorers

414
00:25:53,044 --> 00:25:56,161
from the 15th century set foot
in the New World.

415
00:26:01,924 --> 00:26:04,802
This is Cape Spear, not Cape Fear, mind you.

416
00:26:04,884 --> 00:26:06,237
Cape Spear.

417
00:26:06,524 --> 00:26:11,837
And the main reason l'm here
is that this is the most easterly point

418
00:26:11,924 --> 00:26:13,277
of North America.

419
00:26:13,404 --> 00:26:17,238
The nicest thing about it is you can see that
