425
00:26:32,164 --> 00:26:36,077
And you can pull fish in.
And that brought thousands of people.

426
00:26:36,724 --> 00:26:40,000
Thousands to get the cod.

427
00:26:44,444 --> 00:26:47,800
For over 500 years,
fishing has been the lifeblood here.

428
00:26:47,884 --> 00:26:50,444
Generations of mainly
English and Irish immigrants

429
00:26:50,524 --> 00:26:53,641
give St John's a lively feel
that I instantly liked.

430
00:26:57,604 --> 00:27:00,641
I've headed down to the harbour
for a look-see.

431
00:27:01,804 --> 00:27:05,114
See, l've always liked docks since
l was a wee boy in Glasgow.

432
00:27:05,204 --> 00:27:07,798
They have a peculiar smell.
The smell of ropes,

433
00:27:07,884 --> 00:27:10,523
tar, wood, sawdust.

