I'm going to the Quirpon Lighthouse,
which is only about half an hour away.

692
00:41:10,764 --> 00:41:13,597
But it's the most northerly bit
of Newfoundland.

693
00:41:13,884 --> 00:41:16,398
And it's famous for whale-spotting.

694
00:41:16,844 --> 00:41:19,722
As soon as you say,
''lt's famous for whale-spotting,''

695
00:41:19,804 --> 00:41:22,238
you get the feeling that
all the whales go, ''Right...''

696
00:41:22,684 --> 00:41:24,197
and dive.

697
00:41:25,404 --> 00:41:28,840
Some people are good
at spotting them spouting.

698
00:41:28,924 --> 00:41:31,961
l would have been a lousy whaler.

699
00:41:32,044 --> 00:41:35,195
l don't see it till half the tail is
flapping over my boat.

700
00:41:35,844 --> 00:41:39,678
# Oh, for the life of the rolling seas #

701
00:41:41,004 --> 00:41:42,915
Whoa!

702
00:41:45,964 --> 00:41:49,877
Suddenly the full Newfoundland breakfast
isn't such a good idea.

703
00:41:53,684 --> 00:41:56,152
More scrambled eggs for me, please.

704
00:41:56,244 --> 00:41:59,395
Nurse, the screens. Nurse!

705
00:42:00,764 --> 00:42:02,197
Oh, nurse!

706
00:42:03,084 --> 00:42:05,552
No more black pudding for me!

707
00:42:09,324 --> 00:42:11,838
Apparently there's a whale up ahead.

708
00:42:14,484 --> 00:42:18,602
Oh, l saw it blowing there.
l'm going to shout ''There she blows,''

709
00:42:18,684 --> 00:42:20,834
the next time it happens.

710
00:42:21,124 --> 00:42:23,274
lt's always nice, isn't it,

711
00:42:23,964 --> 00:42:26,956
to see a whale? lt's always such a privilege.

712
00:42:27,964 --> 00:42:30,637
MAN: Tail's coming, there it is. Look.

713
00:42:31,604 --> 00:42:33,674
BlLLY: Oh! l saw it there.

714
00:42:34,284 --> 00:42:36,752
That was just amazing.

715
00:42:39,404 --> 00:42:42,202
Now, this is what I call
getting away from it all.

716
00:42:42,284 --> 00:42:47,039
I'm going to spend my last night in the most
remote lighthouse in Newfoundland.

717
00:42:47,564 --> 00:42:50,920
l ordered a white stretch limo with colour TV.

718
00:42:51,804 --> 00:42:53,442
Didn't show up.

719
00:42:54,924 --> 00:42:58,041
l've been booked into some weird places
in my time.

720
00:42:58,364 --> 00:42:59,479
This takes the biscuit.

721
00:42:59,564 --> 00:43:00,633
WOMAN: Hello!

722
00:43:00,724 --> 00:43:02,282
-BlLLY: Hello!
-Welcome to the island.

723
00:43:02,364 --> 00:43:04,320
Thank you very, very much indeed.

724
00:43:04,404 --> 00:43:06,793
l never entered a hotel quite like that
in my life.

725
00:43:06,884 --> 00:43:07,873
Okay.

726
00:43:08,324 --> 00:43:10,758
Do people usually look as amazed as l do?

727
00:43:11,724 --> 00:43:13,123
WOMAN: l don't know.

728
00:43:27,924 --> 00:43:30,882
We're at the very northern tip
of Newfoundland.

729
00:43:30,964 --> 00:43:34,400
From here, we're going north and west.

730
00:43:35,644 --> 00:43:37,874
And it just seems like
the most extraordinary journey.

731
00:43:37,964 --> 00:43:39,955
We've hardly started yet.

732
00:43:41,484 --> 00:43:44,078
When you think of everything
we've done together,

733
00:43:44,164 --> 00:43:47,361
we've seen fantastic scenery
in this immense country.

734
00:43:47,444 --> 00:43:49,435
There was Pier 21,

735
00:43:49,524 --> 00:43:51,799
fishing at sea with Bobby and Ralph,

736
00:43:51,884 --> 00:43:54,352
the stirring massed bands
at the Highland Games,

737
00:43:54,444 --> 00:43:57,595
the delightful Chester
and his bizarre scarecrows,

738
00:43:57,684 --> 00:44:00,642
having a laugh with Dave
on the River Gander.

739
00:44:01,044 --> 00:44:02,397
Welcome to Newfoundland, my son.

740
00:44:02,484 --> 00:44:06,716
Ordinary folk, generous, warm people
just getting on with their lives,

741
00:44:06,804 --> 00:44:11,480
but clinging on nostalgically to a world
that seems to be slipping away from them.

742
00:44:11,564 --> 00:44:15,523
What will I find as I head for a land
where the going gets really tough?

743
00:44:15,604 --> 00:44:19,756
How are the people up there coping
as the world changes around them?

744
00:44:21,364 --> 00:44:25,118
From here, we're going that way.

745
00:44:26,404 --> 00:44:29,714
Into the wilderness, up to Baffin Island.

746
00:44:31,244 --> 00:44:34,600
If you're stuck for where Baffin Island is,
get yourself a map.

747
00:44:34,684 --> 00:44:37,835
It's slightly left
and a wee bit below Greenland.

748
00:44:38,324 --> 00:44:42,681
The people look different, sound different,
behave different.

749
00:44:42,844 --> 00:44:45,199
That is extraordinary.

750
00:44:45,604 --> 00:44:47,401
You won't believe it.

751
00:44:47,884 --> 00:44:51,240
lt's an absolute sensation.

752
00:44:52,364 --> 00:44:54,355
Why don't you come with me?
We'll have a laugh.

753
00:45:01,884 --> 00:45:05,877
Excuse me, do you have any idea
where l can post a postcard here?

754
00:45:09,924 --> 00:45:11,437
See you later.


